In this press gaggle, Deputy Press Secretary Bill Burton provides updates on the Gulf oil spill and the President's involvement. He mentions that the President has been receiving regular briefings about the situation from Deputy Chief of Staff Jim Messina, who is in contact with Carol Browner on the ground. Secretary Chu is also at the command center in Houston. When asked about the status of the "top kill" operation, Burton says that the President has been receiving updates on it but does not have specific information. He emphasizes the President's frustration with the situation and his commitment to addressing the environmental disaster. Burton also discusses the President's upcoming visit to the Gulf and his plans in Chicago. Other topics touched upon include climate change legislation, offshore drilling, and the President's meeting with Prime Minister Netanyahu. The press gaggle concludes with questions about the Department of Justice's involvement in investigating Congressman Sestak's claims and the President's meeting with Senate Republicans.